new file mode 100644
index 0000000..6b5994d
--- /dev/null
+++ b/RIGGING.md
@@ -0,0 +1,57 @@
+# Rigging
+
+Project tooling values for Shipshape roles. Values only, not procedure.
+Procedure lives in the skills. Every role reads this on open.
+
+## Stack
+
+- language: JavaScript
+- runtime: Node.js
+- packageManager: npm
+
+## Directories
+
+- implementation: src
+- specs: features
+- verification: features/support
+- assets: data
+- scantlings: none
+
+## Commands
+
+- discover: `npx cucumber-js --dry-run --tags "not @captain and not @shipwright"`
+- focused: `npx cucumber-js "$(echo '{scenario}' | cut -d':' -f1)" --name "$(echo '{scenario}' | cut -d':' -f2-)" --tags "not @captain and not @shipwright"`
+- broad: `npx cucumber-js --tags "not @sandbox and not @captain and not @shipwright"`
+- coverage: `npx c8 --reporter=json --reports-dir=coverage npx cucumber-js --tags "not @sandbox and not @captain and not @shipwright"`
+- step-usage: `npx cucumber-js --format usage-json`
+- plank-inventory: `npx jsdoc -X src`
+- typecheck: none
+- lint: none
+- conformance: none
+
+## Perturbation
+
+- message: `PERTURBATION: consider current durable context; remove when fixed`
+- perturb: `throw new Error("PERTURBATION: consider current durable context; remove when fixed");`
+
+## Tiers
+
+- default: @logic
+- sandbox: none
+- policy: @logic default, no credentials
+- weather: .wake/weather.json
+- runrecord: .wake/runrecord.json
+
+## Dependencies
+
+- policy: locked
+- dependency: @cucumber/cucumber ^13.0.0
+- dependency: c8 ^12.0.0
+- dependency: jsdoc ^4.0.5
+- dependency: knip ^6.29.0
+
+## Outbound
+
+- outbound: none
+- ship: none
+- verify: none
diff --git a/features/shipshape.feature b/features/shipshape.feature
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..4374478
--- /dev/null
+++ b/features/shipshape.feature
@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+Feature: Shipshape methodology conformance
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: watchbill.json shape is valid when present
+    Given a watchbill.json exists
+    Then every watch is named watch1, watch2, and so on
+    And every entry is a repo-root-relative scenario reference or a tier tag
+    And the file contains no prose or metadata
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: no standing perturbation token remains in implementation code
+    Given the implementation directory is scanned
+    Then no file contains the literal token "PERTURBATION"
+
+  @captain @conformance
+  Scenario: verification support does not write outside the project tree
+    Given the verification harness runs
+    Then no files are created outside the project root
